<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL _ (Moved in ``i'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-DRUG-ARREST (Newark, N.J.) _ Capping years of quiet
investigation in a case that has roiled relations with Mexico, U.S.
prosecutors detail a 25-count narcotics and money laundering
indictment of Mario Ruiz Massieu, a politically influential former
Mexican deputy attorney general arrested in New Jersey in 1995. By
Ronald Smothers. 1,600 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL _ GENERAL (Moved in ``a'' category) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   NY-ENVIRON (Albany, N.Y.) _ After years of battling over
smokestack pollution that blows from the Midwest and the South, the
Northeast states, led by New York, have signaled for the first time
a willingness to retreat significantly from their demands that
other states reduce emissions. By Richard Perez-Pena. 1,300 words.
</P>
<P>
   MAINE-FISHFARM (Blue Hill, Maine) _ What seems like a typical
squabble between Maine environmental types and a big fish farming
enterprise is actually a glimpse at a bigger struggle as the
American fish industry grows. A giant fishing outfit, Atlantic
Salmon of Maine, the largest producer of farmed salmon in the
country, is proposing a new fish farm next to an island across from
the town of Blue Hill. It has run up against furious resistance
from residents, who cite worries about the environment and public
health. By Carey Goldberg. 2,000 words.
</P>
