<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-CARDS _ ST. LOUIS _ Coverage of the Braves vs. St.
Louis Cardinals. (Rogers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). EDS: First
pitch is at 1:15 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-STADIUMS _ One by one in the 1960s or 1970s, their sacred
walls were rocked by wrecking balls instead of baseballs. Crosley,
Ebbets and Forbes fields. The Polo Grounds, Sportsman's Park and
the rest. They were replaced by multi-purpose flying-saucer
stadiums or domed facilities. Now, the trend is for new-old
ballparks that resemble their distant forefathers _ minus the bad
sight lines, sparse restrooms and lack of luxury boxes. Of
baseball's six oldest major-league ballparks, three will be gone
after this year: Tiger Stadium in Detroit, Milwaukee County Stadium
and San Francisco's 3Com Park, formerly known as Candlestick. In
Boston, Fenway Park is fading fast, and although New York's Yankee
Stadium and Chicago's Wrigley Field are safe now, both could vanish
in a flash. (Moore, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BBO-STADIUMS-CANDLESTICK _ SAN FRANCISCO _ Mark Twain died
nearly five decades before the Giants moved from New York to San
Francisco. To paraphrase the noted humorist, however, the coldest
winter that anybody could spend would be to attend a baseball game
at Candlestick Point. No ballpark in the majors is more affected by
Mother Nature than Candlestick _ or 3Com, as it's been known since
1995 _ where games often are played in swirling winds, brutal
temperatures, blinding fog or all three. (Moore, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-STADIUMS-COUNTY _ MILWAUKEE _ It doesn't have Wrigley's ivy
or the legendary right-field porch of Tiger Stadium. A Green
Monster? The most striking thing involving that color inside County
Stadium was the Packers, but they eventually left to play all of
their games in Green Bay. Imagine an often chilly and an eternally
gray building in the middle of a parking lot. It's either one of
the city's abandoned breweries or County Stadium. (Moore, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-STADIUMS-FENWAY _ BOSTON _ One of baseball's myths is that
everybody loves Fenway Park. Many do, of course. In fact, most who
know the difference between Carl Yastrzemski and a bowl of clam
chowder tend to view this quaint home of the Red Sox as perfection
on earth. But more than a few New Englanders say it's time to rid
their historic landscape of a relic that is cramped and rickety.
(Moore, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-STADIUMS-TIGER _ DETROIT _ With apologies to Fenway Park,
Tiger Stadium is the most magical ballpark this side of Wrigley
Field. They have played baseball at the corner of Michigan and
Trumbull avenues for 103 years, including the last 88 seasons in
Tiger Stadium. (Moore, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-STADIUMS-WRIGLEY _ CHICAGO _ It's the All-Star Game in
Boston, and Ernie Banks loses his smile for the first time ever. A
guy from Atlanta just asked the Hall of Famer if he thinks somebody
will do the unthinkable some day by yanking the ivy _ and
everything else _ out of Wrigley Field. ``I don't think they'll
ever tear down Wrigley Field,'' Banks says. ``It will withstand the
test of time and the history of baseball.'' (Moore, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-STADIUMS-YANKEE _ NW YORK _ The new Yankee Stadium isn't the
old Yankee Stadium. For decades, the House that Ruth Built featured
a copper facade along its majestic roof. This was long before they
altered the ballpark in the mid-1970s, lowering the playing field,
shortening the home-run distances in all but right field and adding
escalator towers. What didn't change was the ghosts. Next to Notre
Dame Stadium, no American sports facility has more ghosts than
Yankee Stadium. (Moore, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   OLYMPICS
</P>
<P>
   OLY-MARTINO _ MILLEDGEVILLE, GA. _ Angel Martino has been to two
Olympics, won six medals and given birth to a son. Yet she still
feels capable of making the 2000 Sydney Games, where she wants to
become the oldest swimming gold medalist in history. Because there
is no 50-meter pool in Milledgeville, a pool builder has donated a
50-meter, two-lane, above-ground pool, which sits in the Martinos'
backyard. (Rosen, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
