<P>
   &QL; 
ENDANGERED-RIVER _ One of the last free-flowing rivers in the
Southwest, the San Pedro could be sucked dry by population growth
in southeast Arizona. The river, which runs from Mexico north for
140 miles until it empties into the Gila River, is among the
biological treasures of North America. By KATHLEEN INGLEY. Story
will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
