urging viewers to turn off their television sets for an entire
week, beginning Sept. 12. The repsonse to the boycott will likely
be as diverse as the Latino community itself. By LAURA TRUJILLO.
Story will move in the ``A'' and ``E'' categories. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN _ (Phoenix) _ It's been heartwarming to witness the
concern expressed by so many God-fearing individuals toward a
troubled Arizona girl. Everyone from nationally syndicated radio
host Dr. Laura Schlessinger to presidential candidate Steve Forbes
has taken up her cause. Because they're all honorable people, I'm
willing to take them at their word when they say they care about
children then invoke God's name. Because I believe them, however, I
must ask: Where in God's name have they been for the past nine
years? The girl has been a ward of the court since she was five
years old. By EJ MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K''
categories. &QL; 
