<HEADLINE>
OHIO STATE-MIAMI CAPSULE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By WENDELL BARNHOUSE 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
\Nsubheds:No. 12 Miami (Fla.) (0-0) vs. No. 9 Ohio State (0-0)
1:30 p.m., WFAA/Channel 8
<TEXT>
<P>
   Location: Giants Stadium, East Rutherford, N.J.
</P>
<P>
   What you need to know: This is the 17th annual Kickoff Classic.
The Buckeyes are coming off an 11-1 season, while the Hurricanes
were 9-3 last season. Both teams won their bowl games. The teams
have met once before, with Ohio State winning, 10-0, in 1977. Each
team will receive $650,000 or 30 percent of the gross revenues for
playing the game.
</P>
<P>
   Keep an eye on: Miami _ QB Kenny Kelly, RB James Jackson, LB Dan
Morgan. Ohio State _ QB Austin Moherman, RB Michael Wiley, LB Na'il
Diggs.
</P>
<P>
   Miami update: The Hurricanes will start an inexperienced
backfield. Kelly takes over for Scott Covington while Jackson will
start in place of Edgerrin James at tailback. ... This will be the
15th time Miami will open against a ranked opponent. The last time
that happened was 1992, when the Hurricanes won at 23rd-ranked
Iowa. ... Of the 99 players on the roster, 60 are freshmen or
sophomores.
</P>
<P>
   Ohio State update: The Buckeyes won a coin toss and are the home
team. ... Moherman (pronounced: MAH-ker-man) is making his first
start. The California native has attempted just one pass. ... The
Buckeyes have won 12 consecutive season openers. Their last loss in
the opener came to Alabama in the 1986 Kickoff Classic.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
